---
import TopNavigation from '../components/TopNavigation.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

const title = 'Julien Dendauw';
---
<style lang="scss">
    .intro {
        grid-area: hero;
        min-height: calc(100vh - 40px);
        background-color: var(--blue-extra-lite);
        background-image: url('/assets/images/coding.svg');
        background-repeat: no-repeat;
        background-attachment: fixed;
        background-position: top;
        color: var(--white);

        @media screen and (min-width: 1260px) {
            background-position: right;
            background-attachment: fixed;
        }

        .introContent {
            position: absolute;
            top: 65%;
            padding: 20px 15px;
            width: 100%;
            font-family: Comfortaa, sans-serif;

            h2 {
                font-size: 2rem;
                margin-bottom: 10px;
            }

            p {
                font-size: 1.6rem;
      
                .caret {
                    display: none;
                }
            }


            @media screen and (min-width: 768px) {
                top: 80%;
                h2 {
                    font-size: 3.5rem;
                }
                p {
                    font-size: 2rem;

                    .caret {
                        display: inline;
                    }
                }
            }

            @media screen and (min-width: 1260px) { 
                top: 50%;
                width: 50%;
                h2 {
                    font-size: 5rem;
                }
                p {
                    font-size: 2.5rem;
                }
            }
        }
    }

</style>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <meta name="description" content="Julien Dendauw has a portfolio?! Even a blog?! Yes and I'm trying to make complex topics easier to gasp with byte-sized posts!">
    <meta name="author" content="Julien Dendauw">
    <title>{title}</title>
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg">
    <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href={Astro.resolve('../styles/global.scss')}>

    <!-- Open Graph / Facebook -->
    <meta property="og:type" content="website">
    <meta property="og:url" content="https://dendauw.tech/">
    <meta property="og:title" content="Julien Dendauw">
    <meta property="og:description" content="Julien Dendauw has a portfolio?! Even a blog?! Yes and I'm trying to make complex topics easier to gasp with byte-sized posts!">
    <meta property="og:image" content="https://dendauw.tech/assets/images/site-metadata.png">
</head>
<body>
    <TopNavigation />
        <div class="intro">
            <div class="introContent center">
                <div class="introText">
                    <h2>Hello, I'm Julien</h2>
                    <p><span class="caret">_</span>A swiss-army knife developer from Belgium</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    <main>
<section>
            <h3>INTRODUCTION</h3>
            <p>
                Welcome to my website. It uses <a href="https://astro.build/">Astro</a> as a framework. It's mainly used to gather my <a href="/thoughts">thoughts</a> for now, hopefully I'll add some more work on this.
                <br>You can <a href="https://github.com/Dauwbot/astro_portfolio/tree/develop">read the source-code of this website on Github</a>. If you would like to reach out, you can always <a href="mailto:julien@dendauw.tech?subject=ðŸ¤˜ - Mail from dendauw.tech">send me an email</a>.
            </p>
            <h4>The Tech stack</h4>
            <p>
                The web is getting more intricate by the day and <a href="https://motherfuckingwebsite.com/">going back</a> to <a href="http://bettermotherfuckingwebsite.com/">simpler times</a> is something <a href="https://thebestmotherfucking.website/">we could all benefit</a> from, like in our everyday lives! ðŸŒ±

            </p>
            <p>
                I'm trying to keep it as clean as possible. I'm not here to sell anything to you. I just want to discuss subjects that are interesting when you're a starting developer.
                <br>I chose Astro because:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>I wanted a static website for SEO. Who knows maybe this will be a hit!</li>
                <li>I feel like side projects should be fun and not related to work: I've been using React & Angular at work for quite some time and I wanted to come back to an ecosystem where I can write big fat HTML files without worrying about the latest trend</li>
                <li>I wanted to learn multiple frameworks and amazingly <a href="https://astro.build/">Astro</a> can run
                    <a href="https://astro-docs-preview.vercel.app/core-concepts/component-hydration">components</a> from all the big guys out here!</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
    </main>
    <Footer />
    </body>
</html>
